contentrichtext.text: '''Eagle Butte''' is an [[impact crater]] in [[Alberta]], Canada, named for a [[Eagle Butte, Alberta|rural area]] west of the [[Cypress Hills (Canada)|Cypress Hills]]. It is 10 km in diameter and the age is estimated to be less than 65 million years ([[Paleocene]] or earlier). The crater is not exposed at the surface.<ref>{{cite Earth Impact DB | name = Eagle Butte| linkname = eagle-butte| accessdate = 2009-08-19}}</ref> ==References== {{reflist}} ==External links== *[http://ottawa-rasc.ca/wiki/index.php?title=Odale_Articles_Eagle_Butte Aerial Exploration of the Eagle Butte impact structure] {{Coord|display=title|name=Eagle Butte crater|49|42|N|110|30|W|type:landmark_scale:300000}} {{Impact cratering on Earth}} [[Category:Cypress County, Alberta]] [[Category:Impact craters of Alberta]] [[Category:Paleocene impact craters]] {{Alberta-geo-stub}} {{Canada-geology-stub}}
